(4700, '2006-12-14', 'Medieval Ii: Total War Update Released', '<div class=\"post_content\" id=\"content_868\" style=\"display: none;\">
<p>Updates to Medieval II: Total War have been released. The updates will be applied automatically when your Steam client is restarted. The specific changes include:<br/><br/><b>Medieval II: Total War</b><br/><ul style=\"padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><li>Multiplayer in-game soft-locks removed<br/><li>Battle AI, Siege AI and Campaign AI are no-longer passive<br/><li>Close-range AI attacks are more consistent<br/><li>Cavalry Charge and Cavalry power are more consistent<br/><li>Merchant trade values no-longer drop after load / save<br/><li>Elephant Artillery does not cause problems in Campaign Battle</li></li></li></li></li></li></ul></p>
<br clear=\"left\"/>
</div>'),
(4700, '2006-12-14', NULL, '<div class=\"details\" id=\"December 14, 2006\" style=\"display: block;\">
Changes/Additions
	<ul>
<li> Multiplayer in-game soft-locks removed</li> <li> Battle AI, Siege AI and Campaign AI are no-longer passive</li> <li> Close-range AI attacks are more consistent</li> <li> Cavalry Charge and Cavalry power are more consistent</li> <li> Merchant trade values no-longer drop after load / save</li> <li> Elephant Artillery does not cause problems in Campaign Battle</li> <li> Reduced Inquisitor power</li> <li> Morale effects tweaked</li> <li> Increased effectiveness of naval invasions</li> <li> Added support for international Multiplayer</li> <li> Missions do not repeat</li> <li> Tweaks made to Diplomacy mechanic</li> <li> Sieged Settlements no-longer showing as sieged even if besieging army has been defeated</li> <li> Gunpowder units do not get stuck re-forming</li> <li> Siege equipment does not disappear while zooming</li> <li> Fixed Assassin exploit</li> <li> Tweaks made to unit pathfinding in settlements</li> <li> No-longer possible to open gates with siege towers or embed them in walls</li> <li> Minor UI changes</li> <li> Added missing Audio triggers</li> <li> Controls and Camera tweaks</li> <li> Added ModTool - Unpacker</li> </ul>
Bug fixes
	<ul>
<li> Fixed Multiplayer lobby crashes</li> <li> Minor issues with deployment lines / zones have been solved</li> </ul>
</div>'),
(4700, '2007-05-08', 'Medieval Ii: Total War Update Released', '<div class=\"post_content\" id=\"content_1033\" style=\"display: none;\">
<p>Updates to Medieval II: Total War have been released. The updates will be applied automatically when your Steam client is restarted. The specific changes include:<br/><br/><b>Medieval II: Total War</b><br/><ul style=\"padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><li>Soft-locks in Multiplayer Lobby no-longer occur<br/><li>Fixed Random hangs after loading Campaign save game<br/><li>Fixed Auto-resolve Siege battle hangs<br/><li>Units do not clump together when told to complete a 180 degree turn<br/><li>Enemy AI army formations in bridge battles now allow their own artillery to fire<br/><li>Improved diplomacy mechanic - AI Factions now stick with alliances and/or attack \'more intelligently\'</li></li></li></li></li></li></ul></p>
<br clear=\"left\"/>
</div>'),
(4700, '2007-08-28', 'Total War Series Expands On Steam', '<div class=\"post_content\" id=\"content_1172\" style=\"display: ;\">
<p>Three new installments in the multi-award-winning Total War franchise (The Creative Assembly/Sega) are now on Steam. <br/><br/><a href=\"http://storefront.steampowered.com/v/index.php?area=game&amp;AppId=4780\">Medieval II: Total War Kingdoms</a>, the official expansion to last year\'s award-winning Medieval II: Total War, is the most content-rich expansion ever produced for a Total War game. Kingdoms presents players with all-new territories to explore, troops to command, and enemies to conquer.<br/><br/>Rome: Total War™ is an epic-scale strategy game that invites you to experience the grandeur, glory and brutality that was ancient Rome. <a href=\"http://storefront.steampowered.com/v/index.php?area=game&amp;AppId=4760\">Rome: Total War - Gold</a> includes Barbarian Invasion, the first official expansion pack. <br/><br/>Also available is the <a href=\"http://www.steampowered.com/v/index.php?area=package&amp;SubId=463\">Rome: Total War - Complete Pack</a>, which includes Rome: Total War - Gold and <a href=\"http://www.steampowered.com/v/index.php?area=game&amp;AppId=4770\">Rome: Total War - Alexander</a>, the second official expansion pack - together for one low price. This add-on pack casts players as one of history’s most brilliant generals, Alexander the Great, handing them the opportunity to replicate his all-conquering achievements and tactical genius on the battlefield.<br/><br/>Note: Games are not available outside North and South America.</p>
<br clear=\"left\"/>
</div>');
